{"key":"processedPost-6190785","value":{"id":6190785,"first":6189795,"last":28082494,"when":1161368919,"utime":"10/20/06 09:28 PM","content":"You can dump your used coffee grinds every morning into a tub and spread them around so they'll dry.  Drying within a few hours is key.  Once dry, they'll keep indefintlely.  <br /><br />It was finding mold on a cup of coffee that had been left out for a weekend that led to my first coffee experiments.  There's a long thread on it in the cultivation archives.<br /><br />There's now a commercial oyster growing operation in Seattle where the guy goes to all the Starbucks every afternoon and collects the used coffee grinds from them for free, then grows oysters on a<br />combination of straw and coffee grinds.<br />RR","title":"Re: Coffee Grounds","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}